{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e61fb72b-9e48-4634-ae84-2d92d6f5b4b1","content":"No `SettingsPage.xaml` exists in the workspace, so I'll provide the conversion pattern directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage` (or any element that sets `BindingContext`). This tells the XAML compiler the type of the binding context, enabling compile-time validation.\n\n**Before:**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**After (compiled bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n## Key changes\n\n1. **Add an XML namespace** pointing to the ViewModel's CLR namespace (`xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"`).\n2. **Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** on the `ContentPage` element.\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, the XAML compiler resolves bindings at compile time. Misspelled or missing properties (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) produce **build errors** automatically — no extra configuration needed.\n\nTo ensure this is fully active:\n\n- **Don't disable XAML compilation.** Confirm your project does *not* have `[XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Skip)]`.\n- **Treat warnings as errors** (optional but recommended): add this to your `.csproj`:\n  ```xml\n  <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n  ```\n- If you need to opt out for a specific binding (e.g., dynamically-typed), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally to disable compiled bindings on that element.\n\nWith these in place, `dotnet build` will fail if any `{Binding ...}` path doesn't match a public property on `SettingsViewModel`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5e9f6e7f-239c-40c6-948d-be12748379e2","outputTokens":703,"requestId":"4831:8197A:761839D:82586DD:69F3FA04"},"id":"122cc4aa-bea2-4799-b4b3-0e04673d0527","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:44.810Z","parentId":"a82a2c16-8dff-4182-9b43-6d3017b41f4b"}
